{
  "texts": [
    "For the elimination of biases, it is crucial to identify all possible biases as well as the cause of their incorporation during the \"AI cycle\" (Fig. 2).",
    "One method includes the bioethical analysis of AI cycles from the initial developmental stages through deployment [36].",
    "The identification and mitigation of biases improve \"AI fairness\"; this implies the equal performance of the AI model across all subgroups in a population [38].",
    "Some measures to ensure clinical AI fairness include panels of AI researchers, clinicians, and ethicists proactively overseeing the process of dataset curation and model training to ensure a clinically fair AI model [32].",
    "Detailed discussions on mitigation of biases in AI is beyond the scope of this paper and can be found elsewhere [36]."
  ]
}